3665pub const TPACKET2_HDRLEN: usize = ((size_of::<crate::tpacket2_hdr>() + TPACKET_ALIGNMENT - 1)
3666    & !(TPACKET_ALIGNMENT - 1))
3667    + size_of::<crate::sockaddr_ll>();
3668pub const TPACKET3_HDRLEN: usize = ((size_of::<crate::tpacket3_hdr>() + TPACKET_ALIGNMENT - 1)
3669    & !(TPACKET_ALIGNMENT - 1))
3670    + size_of::<crate::sockaddr_ll>();

5259pub fn FUTEX_OP(op: c_int, oparg: c_int, cmp: c_int, cmparg: c_int) -> c_int {
5260    ((op & 0xf) << 28) | ((cmp & 0xf) << 24) | ((oparg & 0xfff) << 12) | (cmparg & 0xfff)

5773f! {
5774    pub fn NLA_ALIGN(len: c_int) -> c_int {
5775        return ((len) + NLA_ALIGNTO - 1) & !(NLA_ALIGNTO - 1);
5776    }
5777
5778    pub fn CMSG_NXTHDR(mhdr: *const msghdr, cmsg: *const cmsghdr) -> *mut cmsghdr {
5779        if ((*cmsg).cmsg_len as usize) < size_of::<cmsghdr>() {
5780            return core::ptr::null_mut::<cmsghdr>();
5781        }
5782        let next = (cmsg as usize + super::CMSG_ALIGN((*cmsg).cmsg_len as usize)) as *mut cmsghdr;
5783        let max = (*mhdr).msg_control as usize + (*mhdr).msg_controllen as usize;
5784        if (next.wrapping_offset(1)) as usize > max
5785            || next as usize + super::CMSG_ALIGN((*next).cmsg_len as usize) > max
5786        {
5787            core::ptr::null_mut::<cmsghdr>()
5788        } else {
5789            next
5790        }
5791    }
5792
5793    pub fn CPU_ALLOC_SIZE(count: c_int) -> size_t {
5794        let _dummy: cpu_set_t = mem::zeroed();
5795        let size_in_bits = 8 * size_of_val(&_dummy.bits[0]);
5796        ((count as size_t + size_in_bits - 1) / 8) as size_t
5797    }
5798
5799    pub fn CPU_ZERO(cpuset: &mut cpu_set_t) -> () {
5800        for slot in &mut cpuset.bits {
5801            *slot = 0;
5802        }
5803    }
5804
5805    pub fn CPU_SET(cpu: usize, cpuset: &mut cpu_set_t) -> () {
5806        let size_in_bits = 8 * size_of_val(&cpuset.bits[0]); // 32, 64 etc
5807        let (idx, offset) = (cpu / size_in_bits, cpu % size_in_bits);
5808        cpuset.bits[idx] |= 1 << offset;
5809    }
5810
5811    pub fn CPU_CLR(cpu: usize, cpuset: &mut cpu_set_t) -> () {
5812        let size_in_bits = 8 * size_of_val(&cpuset.bits[0]); // 32, 64 etc
5813        let (idx, offset) = (cpu / size_in_bits, cpu % size_in_bits);
5814        cpuset.bits[idx] &= !(1 << offset);
5815    }
5816
5817    pub fn CPU_ISSET(cpu: usize, cpuset: &cpu_set_t) -> bool {
5818        let size_in_bits = 8 * size_of_val(&cpuset.bits[0]);
5819        let (idx, offset) = (cpu / size_in_bits, cpu % size_in_bits);
5820        0 != (cpuset.bits[idx] & (1 << offset))
5821    }
5822
5823    pub fn CPU_COUNT_S(size: usize, cpuset: &cpu_set_t) -> c_int {
5824        let mut s: u32 = 0;
5825        let size_of_mask = size_of_val(&cpuset.bits[0]);
5826        for i in &cpuset.bits[..(size / size_of_mask)] {
5827            s += i.count_ones();
5828        }
5829        s as c_int
5830    }
5831
5832    pub fn CPU_COUNT(cpuset: &cpu_set_t) -> c_int {
5833        CPU_COUNT_S(size_of::<cpu_set_t>(), cpuset)
5834    }
5835
5836    pub fn CPU_EQUAL(set1: &cpu_set_t, set2: &cpu_set_t) -> bool {
5837        set1.bits == set2.bits
5838    }
5839
5840    pub fn SCTP_PR_INDEX(policy: c_int) -> c_int {
5841        policy >> (4 - 1)
5842    }
5843
5844    pub fn SCTP_PR_POLICY(policy: c_int) -> c_int {

5848    pub fn SCTP_PR_SET_POLICY(flags: &mut c_int, policy: c_int) -> () {
5849        *flags &= !SCTP_PR_SCTP_MASK;
5850        *flags |= policy;
5851    }

5947safe_f! {
5948    pub const fn makedev(major: c_uint, minor: c_uint) -> crate::dev_t {
5949        let major = major as crate::dev_t;
5950        let minor = minor as crate::dev_t;
5951        let mut dev = 0;
5952        dev |= (major & 0x00000fff) << 8;
5953        dev |= (major & 0xfffff000) << 32;
5954        dev |= (minor & 0x000000ff) << 0;
5955        dev |= (minor & 0xffffff00) << 12;
5956        dev
5957    }
5958
5959    pub const fn major(dev: crate::dev_t) -> c_uint {
5960        let mut major = 0;
5961        major |= (dev & 0x00000000000fff00) >> 8;
5962        major |= (dev & 0xfffff00000000000) >> 32;
5963        major as c_uint
5964    }
5965
5966    pub const fn minor(dev: crate::dev_t) -> c_uint {
5967        let mut minor = 0;
5968        minor |= (dev & 0x00000000000000ff) >> 0;
5969        minor |= (dev & 0x00000ffffff00000) >> 12;
5970        minor as c_uint
5971    }

5978        policy == SCTP_PR_SCTP_RTX
5979    }
5980
5981    pub const fn SCTP_PR_PRIO_ENABLED(policy: c_int) -> bool {
5982        policy == SCTP_PR_SCTP_PRIO
5983    }
